The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has confirmed 195 new cases of coronavirus, COVID-19, raising the total to 1,532. The Centre made the confirmation through its Twitter handle @NCDCGov Tuesday night. “195 new cases of #COVID19 reported; 80-Lagos38-Kano15-Ogun15-Bauchi11-Borno10-Gombe9-Sokoto5-Edo5-Jigawa2-Zamfara1-Rivers1-Enugu1-Delta1-FCT1-Nasarawa “As at 11:50pm 28th April- 1532 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria,” the tweet read. It added that while 255 patients have been discharged, 44 are reported dead.